Authorities say the 33-year-old man was caught while conducting speed operations with his colleagues on the N12. JOHANNESBURG - The police in Gauteng have welcomed the arrest of a traffic officer who accepted a bribe from an undercover anti-corruption officer.Police spokesperson Kay Makhubele says that law enforcement officers found to be on the wrong side of the law will not be spared this festive season.Authorities say the 33-year-old man was caught while conducting speed operations with his colleagues on the N12.&quot;Operations which we are intensifying in this festive season, to say that whoever you are, if you are found on the other side so the law, you will be arrested,&quot; Makhubele said.The officer will appear in the Springs Magistrates Court on Wednesday.(Edited by Zunaid Ismael)